  \begin {tikzcd}
    C[S^{-1}]\ar [r, "F_S", dashed, ""{name=S}] & D\makebox [0pt][l]{,}\\
    C\ar [u, "Q"]\ar [ur, "F"', ""{name=F}, bend right]
    \ar [from=F, to=S, draw=none, "\cong ", pos=.3, sloped]
  \end {tikzcd}


 and this F_S is unique up to unique isomorphism, in that the map
\operatorname {Hom}_{D^{C_S}}(-, -)\to  \operatorname {Hom}_{D^C}(-\circ  Q, -\circ  Q) given by
whiskering is bijective.

The universal property of the quotient x/r of a
  congruence r\xrightarrow {r_1,r_2} x is that, for any object z
  equipped with a morphism x\xrightarrow {f} z which is constant on equivalence classes,
  in that fr_1 = fr_2, there exists a unique factorization of x/r\to  z of
  f:





